Just to be safe.

106
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:52,340
♪Love's tide guides,
beyond our mortal space♪

107
00:05:53,240 --> 00:06:02,710
♪A moment kept with your embrace,
where blooms have found their place♪

108
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:11,200
His Majesty
and the Princess Royal have arrived!

109
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:23,320
Greetings, Your Majesty,

110
00:06:23,470 --> 00:06:25,880
Your Highness.

111
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:28,830
You may rise.

112
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,830
Thank you, Your Majesty.

113
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:44,590
Your Majesty.

114
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,830
These are paintings by the noble ladies.

115
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:48,320
Please have a look.

116
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:54,320
Radiant and graceful,
as if exuding a fragrance.

117
00:06:54,830 --> 00:06:55,320
Your Majesty,

118
00:06:55,710 --> 00:06:56,880
this is

119
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,080
"Outshines the Spring Morning"
by Princess Mingyue.

120
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,320
Not bad.

121
00:07:03,350 --> 00:07:04,790
A painting with auspicious signs.

122
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,230
Mingyue's artistry
reflects true mastery.

123
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,030
She shall be rewarded.

124
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:11,030
His Majesty praises Princess Mingyue's

125
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:13,150
"Outshines the Spring Morning"
for its elegance.

126
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,470
The reward is a jade bangle.

127
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,230
I appreciate it, Your Majesty.

128
00:07:22,230 --> 00:07:23,230
Thank you, Brother.

129
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,910
Jiang Si, have you seen it?

130
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:31,830
My will to win

131
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:33,270
makes losing unthinkable.

132
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:40,960
"Heavenly Charm by the Water"

133
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,390
by Kou Lingbo
from the Grand Preceptor's Mansion.

134
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,000
Graceful and refined,
beyond the ordinary.

135
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,909
As expected.

136
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:50,560
"Spring Breeze Rises,"

137
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,470
by Jiang Si, the daughter
of the Count of Dongping.

138
00:07:55,790 --> 00:07:56,270
But...

139
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,150
What is this?

140
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:08,590
Well...

141
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:13,350
We can tolerate a bad painting,

142
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,470
but Jiang Si

143
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,790
submitted a blank sheet of paper!

144
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:20,640
This is utter contempt
of the royal family.

145
00:08:21,230 --> 00:08:22,150
Who is Jiang Si?

146
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:23,320
Send her in.

147
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,880
His Majesty orders

148
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:28,710
Jiang Si
from the Count of Dongping's Mansion.

149
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,590
What about me?

150
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:32,679
Your Highness,

151
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,799
His Majesty only summoned Jiang Si.

152
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,350
I am Jiang Si.

153
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,510
Greetings, Your Majesty.

154
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:41,230
Jiang Si.

155
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:43,960
This is a contest in a palace.

156
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,080
You dare submit a blank sheet of paper?

157
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:47,990
Your Majesty.

158
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:49,200
I spent

159
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,350
two hours on this painting.

160
00:08:50,990 --> 00:08:52,200
It's definitely not blank.

161
00:08:52,830 --> 00:08:53,470
Mr. Sun,

162
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,040
when you inspected the venue,

163
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,800
you saw me painting.

164
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,200
Insolence, Jiang Si!

165
00:08:58,590 --> 00:09:00,630
Not only did you submit nothing,

166
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,110
you even slandered me.

167
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,920
Your Majesty.

168
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,510
Even after an hour, I never saw Jiang Si

169
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:09,400
draw with her brush.

170
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:10,990
In the next hour,

171
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:14,230
I saw her holding her brush,

172
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,750
pretending to be painting.

173
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,320
Show her the painting.

174
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:18,470
Yes.

175
00:09:39,510 --> 00:09:40,200
Stop.

176
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,040
Now is not the time to stand out!

177
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,200
Father,

178
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:44,990
I saw Jiang Si painting

179
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:46,680
with my own eyes.

180
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,320
You sat nowhere near where they painted.

181
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:50,960
How did you see it?

182
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:52,680
Jiang Si attended the banquet.

183
00:09:53,350 --> 00:09:54,830
Why would she submit nothing

184
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,830
just for you to punish her?

185
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,200
Something is off.

186
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,400
Please investigate.

187
00:10:00,710 --> 00:10:01,870
We have concrete evidence.

188
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:03,960
What else can it be?

189
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,280
She has no talents or skills.

190
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:08,800
She submitted nothing
because she could paint nothing.

191
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:09,830
Your Majesty.

192
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:13,560
This painting is indeed my work.

193
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,400
But it's not blank.

194
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,160
Are you implying

195
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:18,990
everyone else here is blind?

196
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:20,870
There is a scent on this paper.

197
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,750
It reeks of a type of grass.

198
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,350
I grew up studying plants.

199
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:28,920
I learned about the plant

200
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:30,200
Traceless Grass.

201
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,160
Mixing ink

202
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,080
with its juice

203
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,590
will make the ink vanish

204
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,960
in less than 15 minutes.

205
00:10:37,830 --> 00:10:38,960
I suspect my ink

206
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,080
had been tampered with

207
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,830
beforehand.

208
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:42,710
Your Majesty.

209
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,470
Could I have a cup of water?

210
00:10:44,830 --> 00:10:45,320
Yes.

211
00:10:47,830 --> 00:10:48,830
Pour it over the painting.

212
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:09,830
How dare you, Jiang Si?

213
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:12,440
Black flowers are only used
for a national funeral!

214
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,870
You insulted us with this painting!

215
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:15,590
Someone!

216
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:17,400
Drag her out and flog her with a rod!

217
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,230
Wait.

218
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:19,400
Please hear me out.

219
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,630
The black peonies

220
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:21,990
are indeed my work.

221
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,350
But I painted the black peonies

222
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:25,710
for a reason.

223
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,960
Fine. Do tell.

224
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,830
I'd like to hear

225
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:30,960
your reason.

226
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,710
The black peonies I painted

227
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:34,800
are not

228
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,080
meant for the guests here.

229
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:38,750
They are meant

230
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:41,800
for the late Empress.

231
00:11:42,990 --> 00:11:44,510
Empress Qingrong loved peonies.

232
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:45,870
Everyone knows that.

233
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,160
Your Majesty had the Imperial Garden

234
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:48,960
filled with peonies

235
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,830
to mourn her passing, am I right?

236
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,920
Empress Qingrong
was kind and compassionate.

237
00:11:55,230 --> 00:11:56,400
She cared about the common people.

238
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:57,680
She advocated frugality

239
00:11:57,990 --> 00:11:58,830
and practiced it.

240
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,440
She was my role model.

241
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,800
She provided education

242
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,560
for the poor.

243
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,400
She founded free dispensaries

244
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:08,830
to save countless lives from disease.

245
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:10,630
Empress Qingrong

246
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,440
was beloved by the people of Zhou.

247
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,230
She is the woman

248
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:15,590
I look up to the most.

249
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:18,750
Today, I name this painting

250
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,800
"Spring Breeze Rises"

251
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:22,470
because

252
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:23,870
the thought of her

253
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:25,510
feels like a spring breeze.

254
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:27,750
Having known greatness,

255
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:30,230
most will pale in comparison.

256
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,400
The Imperial Garden

257
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:34,080
is full of vibrant colors,

258
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,560
but the black peonies

259
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,110
are rare and precious.

260
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:39,830
Not unlike Empress Qingrong,

261
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,280
who is irreplaceable

262
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,440
in Your Majesty's eyes.

263
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:55,630
How thoughtful of you.

264
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,080
Father.

265
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,200
It's a great painting.

266
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:04,470
But due to the tempered ink,

267
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,230
such a thoughtful piece of artwork

268
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,680
could've been lost.

269
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:09,750
Sun Congxin.

270
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,960
How do you explain

271
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,160
Jiang Si's painting?

272
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:16,710
I had no idea the ink would vanish.

273
00:13:17,350 --> 00:13:18,750
I am innocent, Your Majesty!

274
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,750
You were

275
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,710
behind this entire plot.

276
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,040
Why was Miss Jiang

277
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,710
the only one with tempered ink?

278
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,470
Who dares employ such trickery

279
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:28,830
right under my nose?

280
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:30,870
I'd like to examine the ink.

281
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:31,870
Yes.

282
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:41,960
Your Majesty.

283
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:43,630
The ink, brushes, and ink-stones

284
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:45,160
have all been cleaned.

285
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,630
There's nothing left.

286
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,470
Well done, Sun Congxin.

287
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,560
